ar.com/headlines/2015/02/20/1425813/biff-wont-return-saf-weapons-without-rematch-vs-pnp |title=BIFF won't return SAF weapons without rematch vs PNP |publisher=Philstar |date=2015-02-20 |accessdate=2015-10-08}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===Mortars===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-  bgcolor=#B0E0E6\n! style=\"width:3%;\"| Picture\n! style=\"width:10%;\"| Model\n! style=\"width:18%;\"| Origin\n! style=\"width:16%;\"| Type\n! style=\"width:7%;\"| Caliber\n! style=\"width:%;\"| Version\n! style=\"width:35%;\"| Notes\n|-\n| [[File:170514-N-FV745-0256 - Philippine soldier prepares to fire off a mortar round with U.S. Army soldiers.jpg|100px]]|| M75 mortar || {{PHI}} || [[Mortar (weapon)|Mortar]] || 60mm || M75 || Several units carried over from the Philppine Constabulary.<ref>{{Cite report |authorlink= |author=Danilo Lazo & Juanita Mercader |date= |title=The AFP Self-Reliance Defense Posture (SRDP) Program: Leading the Nation Towards a New Direction |url=http://asj.upd.edu.ph/mediabox/archive/ASJ-27-1989/lazomercader.pdf |publisher= |page=151 |docket= |accessdate=2015-10-03 |quote= }}</ref> \n|-\n| [[File:Mortar M29.jpg|100px]] || [[M29 mortar]] || {{USA}} || [[Mortar (weapon)|Mortar]] || 81mm || M29 || Several units carried over from the Philppine Constabulary \n|-\n|}\n\n===Armored Vehicles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-  bgcolor=#B0E0E6\n! style=\"width:3%;\"| Picture\n! style=\"width:10%;\"| Model\n! style=\"width:18%;\"| Origin\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Type\n! style=\"width:8%;\"| Version\n! style=\"width:8%;\"| Units\n! style=\"width:35%;\"| Notes\n|-\n| [[File:PNP SAF V-150.jpg|100px]] || [[Cadillac Gage Commando]] || {{USA}} || [[Armoured personnel carrier]] || V-150 || 28 Units \n| Although the number of active vehicles might be less.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.philstar.com/metro/723895/pnp-asked-allot-p24-m-more-defective-combat-vehicles |title=PNP asked to allot P24 M more for defective combat vehicles |publisher=Philstar |d