0njpcbms8m8osq2b99ekutvtmk</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:M14 rifle - USA - 7,62x51mm - Arm\u00e9museum.jpg|100px]] || [[M14 rifle]] || {{US}} || [[Battle rifle]] || [[7.62\u00d751mm NATO]] || M14 || In service as standard battle rifle. Several units will be undergoing repair and upgrade with the Government Arsenal.\n|-\n|}\n\n===Designated Marksman & Sniper Rifles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-  bgcolor=#B0E0E6\n! style=\"width:3%;\"| Picture\n! style=\"width:10%;\"| Model\n! style=\"width:18%;\"| Origin\n! style=\"width:16%;\"| Type\n! style=\"width:7%;\"| Caliber\n! style=\"width:%;\"| Version\n! style=\"width:35%;\"| Notes\n|-\n| || [[Ferfrans]] SOACR ||  {{USA}} || [[Designated marksman rifle]] || [[7.62\u00d751mm NATO]] || DMR<hr>SOACR 18\" || Earlier models were called Ferfrans DMR.\n|-\n| [[File:PEO M14 EBR.jpg|100px]] || [[Ferfrans]] [[Mk 14 Enhanced Battle Rifle#Civilian|SOPMOD M14 Enhanced Battle Rifle]] || {{USA}} || [[Designated marksman rifle]] || [[7.62\u00d751mm NATO]] || SOPMOD M14 EBR 18.5\"<hr>SOPMOD M14 EBR 22\" || Built by Ferfrans from existing M14 rifles using Sage International M14/M1A EBR Tactical Stock System aluminum chassis but with an M4 buttstock, delivered in 2008.\n|-\n|  || [[United Defense Manufacturing Corporation|UDMC]] F5-DGIS || {{PHI}} || [[Designated marksman rifle]] || [[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]] || F5-DGIS 20\" || 233 units delivered in April 2018.\n|-\n| [[File:Galil-Sniper-Galatz-001.jpg|100px]] || [[IMI Galil]] || {{ISR}} || [[Designated marksman rifle]] / [[Sniper rifle]] || [[7.62\u00d751mm NATO]] || Galatz || In limited numbers.\n|-\n| [[File:SR-25 pic02.jpg|100px]] || [[SR-25]] || {{US}} || [[Sniper rifle]] || [[7.62\u00d751mm NATO]] || Mk.11 Mod 0 ||\n|-\n| [[File:PSG1 and MSG 90.jpg|100px]] || [[Heckler & Koch PSG1]] || {{GER}} || [[Sniper rifle]] || [[7.62\u00d751mm NATO]] || PSG-1 || Limited numbers in service.\n|-\n| [[File:Savage 10FPXP-LEA.jpg|100px]] || [[Savage 10FP]] || {{USA}} || [[Sniper rifle]] || 